## Public Constructors

### DataExtractor() {#a46aa25f9df530608164c58934b2c5f01}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::DataExtractor::DataExtractor (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Data, bool IsLittleEndian, uint8&#95;t AddressSize)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Construct with a buffer that is owned by the caller.

This constructor allows us to use data that is owned by the caller. The data must stay around as long as this object is valid.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h/#l00086">86</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h">DataExtractor.h</a>.

### eof() {#a3ad190d933f6858fe3437ccf63bf8b65}

<MemberDefinition

  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return true iff the cursor is at the end of the buffer, regardless of the error state of the cursor.

The only way both eof and error states can be true is if one attempts a read while the cursor is at the very end of the data buffer.

### getAddress() {#a41d94746913373f82219a1d23e15ce31}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>uint64&#95;t llvm::DataExtractor::getAddress (uint64&#95;t &#42; offset_ptr) const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Extract an pointer from <em>&#42;offset&#95;ptr</em>.

Extract a single pointer from the data and update the offset pointed to by <em>offset&#95;ptr</em>. The size of the extracted pointer is <em><a href="#a727b157e8418a101ec69dcb2e9ceea39">getAddressSize()</a></em>, so the address size has to be set correctly prior to extracting any pointer values.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="[inout] offset_ptr">A pointer to an offset within the data that will be advanced by the appropriate number of bytes if the value is extracted correctly. If the offset is out of bounds or there are not enough bytes to extract this value, the offset will be left unmodified.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
The extracted pointer value as a 64 integer.
</SectionUser>

### getBytes() {#ade9e119455709c0d46a34464ebdbf179}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>StringRef DataExtractor::getBytes (uint64&#95;t &#42; OffsetPtr, uint64&#95;t Length, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> &#42; Err=nullptr) const</>}>
Extract a fixed number of bytes from the specified offset.

Returns a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> for the bytes from the data at the offset pointed to by <em>OffsetPtr</em>. A fixed length C string will be extracted and the <em>OffsetPtr</em> will be advanced by <em>Length</em> bytes.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="[inout] OffsetPtr">A pointer to an offset within the data that will be advanced by the appropriate number of bytes if the value is extracted correctly. If the offset is out of bounds or there are not enough bytes to extract this value, the offset will be left unmodified.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="[in] Length">The number of bytes to extract. If there are not enough bytes in the data to extract all of the bytes, the offset will be left unmodified.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="[inout] Err">A pointer to an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> object. Upon return the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> object is set to indicate the result (success/failure) of the function. If the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> object is already set when calling this function, no extraction is performed.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> for the extracted bytes. If the offset pointed to by <em>OffsetPtr</em> is out of bounds, or if the offset plus the length is out of bounds, a default-initialized <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> will be returned.
</SectionUser>

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h/#l00233">233</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h">DataExtractor.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/dataextractor-cpp/#l00181">181</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/dataextractor-cpp">DataExtractor.cpp</a>.

### getSigned() {#a5cc53bb122d7af1e40b77867d080114d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>int64&#95;t DataExtractor::getSigned (uint64&#95;t &#42; offset_ptr, uint32&#95;t size) const</>}>
Extract an signed integer of size <em>byte&#95;size</em> from <em>&#42;offset&#95;ptr</em>.

Extract a single signed integer value (sign extending if required) and update the offset pointed to by <em>offset&#95;ptr</em>. The size of the extracted integer is specified by the <em>byte&#95;size</em> argument. <em>byte&#95;size</em> should have a value greater than or equal to one and less than or equal to eight since the return value is 64 bits wide. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/any">Any</a> <em>byte&#95;size</em> values less than 1 or greater than 8 will result in nothing being extracted, and zero being returned.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="[inout] offset_ptr">A pointer to an offset within the data that will be advanced by the appropriate number of bytes if the value is extracted correctly. If the offset is out of bounds or there are not enough bytes to extract this value, the offset will be left unmodified.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="[in] size">The size in bytes of the integer to extract.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
The sign extended signed integer value that was extracted, or zero on failure.
</SectionUser>

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h/#l00306">306</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h">DataExtractor.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/dataextractor-cpp/#l00142">142</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/dataextractor-cpp">DataExtractor.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### getUnsigned() {#a091e3b172c8f532c021b21c90fd3d461}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>uint64&#95;t DataExtractor::getUnsigned (uint64&#95;t &#42; offset_ptr, uint32&#95;t byte_size, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> &#42; Err=nullptr) const</>}>
Extract an unsigned integer of size <em>byte&#95;size</em> from <em>&#42;offset&#95;ptr</em>.

Extract a single unsigned integer value and update the offset pointed to by <em>offset&#95;ptr</em>. The size of the extracted integer is specified by the <em>byte&#95;size</em> argument. <em>byte&#95;size</em> should have a value greater than or equal to one and less than or equal to eight since the return value is 64 bits wide. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/any">Any</a> <em>byte&#95;size</em> values less than 1 or greater than 8 will result in nothing being extracted, and zero being returned.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="[inout] offset_ptr">A pointer to an offset within the data that will be advanced by the appropriate number of bytes if the value is extracted correctly. If the offset is out of bounds or there are not enough bytes to extract this value, the offset will be left unmodified.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="[in] byte_size">The size in byte of the integer to extract.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="[inout] Err">A pointer to an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> object. Upon return the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> object is set to indicate the result (success/failure) of the function. If the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> object is already set when calling this function, no extraction is performed.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
The unsigned integer value that was extracted, or zero on failure.
</SectionUser>

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h/#l00273">273</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/dataextractor-h">DataExtractor.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/dataextractor-cpp/#l00126">126</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/dataextractor-cpp">DataExtractor.cpp</a>.

### prepareRead() {#ad55fe6963d08fd0255315215d1d048ad}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool DataExtractor::prepareRead (uint64&#95;t Offset, uint64&#95;t Size, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> &#42; E) const</>}>
If it is possible to read <em>Size</em> bytes at offset <em>Offset</em>, returns <b>true</b>.

Otherwise, returns <b>false</b>. If <em>E</em> is not nullptr, also sets the error object to indicate an error.
